get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/oauth2/authorization/google
  body: none
  auth: none
}

docs {
  # OAuth2 — Sign in with Google

  Entry point of the Google OAuth2 login flow. Hitting this URL in a browser
  redirects the user to Google's consent screen. After consent, Google calls
  back to `/api/login/oauth2/code/google` (handled automatically by Spring
  Security), which then triggers `OAuth2AuthenticationSuccessHandler` and
  redirects the browser to `${app.frontend-url}/`.

  > Bruno cannot replay the full flow because it requires interactive consent
  > on Google's domain. This entry exists to document the endpoint; copy the
  > URL into a browser to actually exercise it.

  ## Behaviour

  - **Browser**: 302 redirect to Google's OAuth consent screen.
  - **Server (after callback)**: creates or links a local user, sets a
    `JSESSIONID` cookie, then 302-redirects to the frontend.

  ## Account resolution rules

  1. If a user already exists with `(provider=GOOGLE, providerId=<sub>)`, returns it.
  2. Else if a user exists with the same email, links the Google identity to that account.
  3. Else creates a new user with `password=null`, `provider=GOOGLE`, a unique pseudo derived from the Google name, and the `USER` role.

  Banned users are rejected with redirect to `/login?error=oauth_banned`.
  Any other failure redirects to `/login?error=oauth_failed`.

  ## Configuration

  Requires `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` to be set in the environment
  (Doppler in dev/prod). Without them the OAuth2 chain is dormant and this URL returns 404.
}
